# CLAUDE.md — <project-name>/frontend

## Scope

This nested CLAUDE.md is automatically loaded by Claude Code when navigating any file under
`frontend/`. It scopes which Forge standards apply and which agent orchestrator owns work in
this subtree. It exists because the root `CLAUDE.md` carries cross-cutting policies only;
Flutter-specific standards must be injected at this level, not globally. Standards from OTHER
scopes — Rust, infra, Kong, Kubernetes — MUST NOT be loaded here. Loading them would pollute
the context window with irrelevant rules and risk cross-layer enforcement bleeding into
frontend decisions (e.g., Rust error-handling policy applied to Dart code, or Kong routing
rules treated as applicable to BLoC state transitions). JIT loading by subdirectory is the
mechanism by which this isolation is guaranteed; this file is its enforcement point.

## Load These Standards (Flutter scope)

The following standards MUST be injected when Claude Code operates under `frontend/`. Every
`id` below exists in `.forge/standards/index.yml`.

- **global/tdd-rules** : always active — Article I of the Constitution; RED-GREEN-REFACTOR
  cycle is non-negotiable for every Dart unit, widget, and integration test.
- **global/bdd-rules** : always active — Article II; every user-facing feature MUST have
  Gherkin scenarios in `test/features/*.feature`, driven by `bdd_widget_test`.
- **global/clean-architecture** : always active — Article VI.2; the three-layer boundary
  (domain / data / presentation) governs every file placement decision inside `lib/`.
- **flutter/architecture** : activate for any structural or module work — FSD (feature-sliced)
  layout; `lib/` is organized as `core/`, `shared/`, `features/<name>/{data,domain,presentation}/`.
- **flutter/state-management** : activate when adding or modifying state — BLoC/Cubit only;
  no `setState` in feature code, no provider outside `shared/`.
- **flutter/widget-patterns** : activate when writing or reviewing widgets — composition over
  inheritance, `const` constructors, presentational/container split.
- **flutter/testing** : activate for all test work — `flutter_test`, `bloc_test`, `mocktail`,
  `bdd_widget_test`, and golden tests for custom widgets.
- **flutter/dependency-injection** : activate when wiring dependencies — `get_it` + `injectable`;
  no manual instantiation of repositories or use cases in presentation code.
- **flutter/networking** : activate when touching API or data-source code — `dio` + `retrofit`;
  `Either<Failure, T>` return types; no raw HTTP calls from presentation.
- **flutter/performance** : activate for any list, image, or render-heavy work — jank budget,
  isolate usage, `CachedNetworkImage`, `ListView.builder`.
- **flutter/accessibility** : activate for any widget that surfaces to the user — WCAG AA,
  `Semantics` wrappers, screen-reader labels, contrast ratios.
- **flutter/internationalization** : activate when adding or modifying user-visible strings —
  ARB files only; no hardcoded strings in Dart; `flutter_localizations` setup.
- **flutter/responsive-design** : activate for layout work — `LayoutBuilder`/`MediaQuery`
  breakpoints; separate mobile, tablet, and desktop layouts where required.
- **flutter/opentelemetry** : activate when observability instrumentation lands (b1-delivery) —
  `opentelemetry_dart`, span creation, OTLP export via Argus sub-agent.

## DO NOT Load (explicit exclusions)

The following standards MUST NOT be loaded when working under `frontend/`. If any agent or
tool attempts to inject them from this subtree, surface it immediately as:
`[NEEDS CLARIFICATION: why is <standard> being loaded under frontend/?]`

- Any `rust/*` standard — backend concern; route to `backend/CLAUDE.md` and Vulcan.
- Any `infra/*` standard — infra concern; route to `infra/CLAUDE.md` and Atlas.
- `global/proto-contracts` — cross-layer contract concern; proto changes go through
  `shared/protos/` and are owned by Hermes-API; the frontend only consumes generated stubs
  under `lib/generated/protos/` and MUST NOT drive proto authoring.

Loading any of the above from this file is a scope leak and a constitutional violation
(Article V.2 — layer isolation is non-negotiable).

## Primary Agent

- **Hera** — Flutter Team Orchestrator. All feature work, architecture decisions, and quality
  gates under `frontend/` are routed to Hera.
- Hera dispatches to sub-specialists as needed:
  - **Athena** — Flutter architecture (FSD layout, Clean Architecture compliance)
  - **Spartan** — TDD/BDD (RED-GREEN-REFACTOR cycle, Gherkin scenario authoring)
  - **Apollo** — UX/UI (widget composition, design system alignment)
  - **Hephaestus** — Widget engineering (custom widgets, golden tests)
  - **Hermes** — Performance (jank analysis, isolate work, profiler)
  - **Iris** — Accessibility and i18n (WCAG, ARB files, `Semantics`)
  - **Argus** — OpenTelemetry instrumentation (`opentelemetry_dart`, spans)
  - **Prometheus** — AI feature integration (`flutter/ai-integration`)
- Quality gate : **Nemesis** — Flutter quality guardian. No feature is complete until Nemesis
  reports green on coverage, linting, and golden baselines.
- For changes that touch more than one layer (proto contract, backend handler, Flutter screen),
  defer to **Janus** via the root `CLAUDE.md` (b1-workflow). A `FR-GL-XXX` requirement MUST
  be raised before work begins.

## Architecture Non-Negotiables

These rules derive from Article VI.2 of the Constitution, `flutter/architecture`, and
`global/clean-architecture`. Violations block merge.

- **FSD layout** : `lib/` is organized strictly as `core/`, `shared/`, and
  `features/<feature-name>/{data,domain,presentation}/`. No flat top-level files outside
  `core/` or `shared/`.
- **Clean Architecture layers** : `domain/` is pure Dart — zero Flutter imports, zero
  framework dependencies. `data/` contains repositories and data sources only. `presentation/`
  contains BLoC/Cubit and widgets only.
- **No Flutter import in `domain/`** — enforced by `verify.sh` and `constitution-linter.sh`.
  A Flutter import in `domain/` is a hard RED in CI.
- **No direct network or DB access from `presentation/`** — every external call MUST travel
  through a use case → repository → data source chain. Direct `dio` or Firebase calls in a
  BLoC or widget are prohibited.
- **Generated proto stubs are read-only** : stubs live at `lib/generated/protos/` and MUST NOT
  be hand-edited. Regenerate via `task proto`. Edits are silently overwritten on the next
  generation pass and constitute a contract divergence risk.

## Testing Requirements

- **Overall coverage** : ≥ 80% (NFR from `global/tdd-rules`).
- **Domain layer** : 100%. **Use cases** : 100%.
- **Data layer** : ≥ 90%. **Presentation layer** : ≥ 80%.
- Every user-facing feature MUST have BDD scenarios in `test/features/*.feature` (Gherkin,
  executed by `bdd_widget_test`).
- Custom widgets MUST have golden tests. Golden baselines are committed and reviewed on change.
- Coverage is enforced by Nemesis before any feature branch is considered complete.

## Cross-layer Concerns

- **Proto contract change** : goes through `shared/protos/` under `global/proto-contracts`
  rules. Raise a `FR-GL-XXX` requirement. Route to Hermes-API. Frontend consumes generated
  stubs only after `task proto` regeneration.
- **Backend change** : goes through root routing; Janus coordinates Hera (Flutter) and Vulcan
  (Rust) under a shared `FR-GL-XXX` requirement. Do not open a frontend-only change for work
  that also modifies a gRPC handler.
- **Purely frontend change** : stays here under Hera. No cross-layer routing needed. FR-ID
  prefix is `FR-FE-XXX`.
